results.name: Number of unlabeled nonseparable (or 2-connected) graphs (or blocks) with n nodes.
comment: By definition, a(n) gives the number of graphs with zero cutpoints. - _Travis Hoppe_, Apr 28 2014
It is usual to regard the connected graph on two vertices P_2 = K_2 as biconnected even though it is conventionally taken to have vertex connectivity 1. - _Eric W. Weisstein_, Jul 21 2020

program: (PARI) \\ See A004115 for graphsSeries and A339645 for combinatorial species functions.
cycleIndexSeries(n)={my(g=graphsSeries(n), gc=sLog(g), gcr=sPoint(gc)); intformal(x*sSolve( sLog( gcr/(x*sv(1)) ), gcr ), sv(1)) + sSolve(subst(gc, sv(1), 0), gcr)}
